                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="200127" author="yujian" created="Sat, 24 Jun 2017 06:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Andreas,&lt;br/&gt;
I found this issue while investigating &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9663&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_103a: LU-2561 test failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9663&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9663&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="200126" author="adilger" created="Sat, 24 Jun 2017 06:05:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not a bug. While the file is in the client cache, we don&apos;t know how much space it will actually use on disk so it is just an estimate based on the file size. Once the data is flushed from the client to disk the blocks count reflects the actual space usage on disk. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there some problem that this causes, or just something you noticed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
